<div class="container">
    <div class="jumbotron">
        <div class="row text-center">
            <div class="col col-lg-12 col-sm-12">
                <h1 class="">MapMerge</h1>
                <p>Create simple and easy large map images.</p>
                <%= link_to(  locations_path , :class => "btn btn-success btn-lg" ) do  %>
                <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-map"></span> Start Here
                <% end %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="definitions">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row ">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="panel panel-success">
                    <div class="panel-heading ">
                        What is MapMerge
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>Mapmerge is a free Google Maps based tool to create Large Location Maps which are used in architecture office`s. Architects use such Maps to plan, design and create things which only can could be understood by architects. :P </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="panel panel-success">
                    <div class="panel-heading ">
                        How to use Mapmerge?
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">

                        <p>Just click on the map and configurate your location settings (zoomfaktor, tiles ,etc...) or choose a location by typing the address in the search fields.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="panel panel-success">
                    <div class="panel-heading ">
                        Why YOU should use MapMerge?
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <p>Just to save houers of work in Photoshop. </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
